<Link id="l02391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2391"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02392" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2392"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// guessLibraryShortName() is passed a name of a dynamic library and returns a</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02397" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2397"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      Foo.framework/Foo</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02398" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2398"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Where A and Foo can be any string.  And may contain a trailing suffix</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02399" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2399"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// starting with an underbar.  If the Name is recognized as a framework then</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2405"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// one of the two following forms:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2406"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      libFoo.A.dylib</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2407"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      libFoo.dylib</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2408"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2409"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The library may have a suffix trailing the name Foo of the form:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2410"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      libFoo&#95;profile.A.dylib</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2411"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      libFoo&#95;profile.dylib</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02418" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2418"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Suffix values. Calling code needs to be tolerant of guessLibraryShortName()</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l03182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3182"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We have a trie data structure and need a way to walk it that is compatible</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3183"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// with the C++ iterator model. The solution is a non-recursive depth first</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03184" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3184"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// traversal where the iterator contains a stack of parent nodes along with a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03185" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3185"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// string that is the accumulation of all edge strings along the parent chain</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03186" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3186"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to this point.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03187" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3187"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03188" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3188"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// There is one &quot;export&quot; node for each exported symbol.  But because some</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03189" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3189"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// symbols may be a prefix of another symbol (e.g. &#95;dup and &#95;dup2), an export</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03190" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3190"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// node may have child nodes too.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03191" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3191"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3192"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The algorithm for moveNext() is to keep moving down the leftmost unvisited</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03193" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3193"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// child until hitting a node with no children (which is an export node or</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3194"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// else the trie is malformed). On the way down, each node is pushed on the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03195" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3195"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// stack ivar.  If there is no more ways down, it pops up one and tries to go</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03196" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3196"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// down a sibling path until a childless node is reached.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03197" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3197" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/object/exportentry/#a0ec56e47067ae8d2239c5da9d6ae8418"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/object/exportentry/#a0ec56e47067ae8d2239c5da9d6ae8418">ExportEntry::moveNext</a>() &#123;</span></CodeLine>
